							<p>When I think of the best player I ever played with I have to step back and decide between the best player and the best athlete.  I think people today get these two things mixed up.

							<p>I have been blessed to play with HOF players like Thurman Thomas, Bruce Smith and Andre Reed-all great players and great athletes. But if i had to pick one player that I played with that I think is the best, I would hands down go with cornerback Antoine Winfield. 

							<p>I understand that's not the most obvious choice considering those other Hall of Fame members. But when I think of the 'best' player, I feel he has to be able to play all aspects of his job at "best" level...the pass, the run, play-making ability, and a record of playing big in the biggest games.  

							<p>I remember Antoine as a rookie and how he made an impact the first day in pads, it was play after play after play after play...he either intercepted the pass or made a big hit.  The hits are a huge part of my calculation, because Antoine is 5'8 on a good day but would lay the wood like he was a 6'4 Defensive End.  It was an aspect to his game as a cornerback that he didn't have to have to still be a great cover guy, but it rounds out his resume.  Best is all about MORE.  

							<p>For whatever it's worth, he has stats...1054 tackles, 14 forced fumbles, 8.5 sacks and 27 interceptions.  He played 14 seasons high-level seasons in the NFL at a speed position, which is impressive in itself.  And throughout those 14 seasons, he had a well-earned reputation as one of the hardest hitting defensive backs in football.  

							<p>Some may call him a jack-of-all-trades, I'll just call him the best FOOTBALL PLAYER I ever played with.
							 
